The First Law: Mutual Awareness Prerequisite
“A relationship can only begin and exist when Self is aware of Other, and Other is aware of Self.”
Legal Foundation: This establishes the minimum viable condition for relationship existence - reciprocal consciousness recognition. Without mutual awareness, there is no phenomenological “third entity” - only two separate individuals occupying space.
Implications:
	•	One-way awareness (I see you but you don’t see me) = potential relationship, not actual relationship
	•	Mutual awareness = relationship possibility activated
	•	Sustained mutual awareness = relationship container can be constructed
